          "prompt_html": "<h1>NOTE COMPLETION 21</h1><p><strong>Questions 21 - 26</strong></p><p>Complete the table and the notes.</p><p>Use <strong>NO MORE THAN TWO WORDS AND / OR A NUMBER</strong> for each answer.</p><table><thead><tr><th><strong>Undergraduate Courses</strong></th><th><strong>Duration (all full time)</strong></th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Business Studies</td><td>4 years</td></tr><tr><td>Advertising</td><td>3 years</td></tr><tr><td>Marketing</td><td>3 years</td></tr><tr><td>Personnel Management</td><td>3 years</td></tr><tr><td><blank data-qid=\"q21\"/></td><td>3 years</td></tr><tr><td>Accountancy</td><td>3 years</td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong>Masters Courses</strong></p><p>Advertising, Marketing, Personnel Management, Finance, Accountancy and general MBA (1 year full time and 2 years part time)</p><p><strong>Business Studies BA Course</strong></p><p>Years 1 and 2: Obligatory modules: economics, research methods, marketing, advertising, operations management, statistics, accountancy, personnel and finance.</p><p>Year 3: working in industry.</p><p>Year 4: Electives: Year 1 and 2 subjects + specialised courses. Only <blank data-qid=\"q22\"/> not offered as an elective from year 1 and 2 subjects.</p><p><strong>Assessment</strong></p><ul><li><p>Years 1, 2 and 4 exams take place at the end of each <blank data-qid=\"q23\"/></p></li><li><p>All exams 2 - 3 hours in length</p></li><li><p>Students can take exams again over the summer</p></li><li><p>Students can only study a whole year again, if there are <blank data-qid=\"q24\"/></p></li><li><p>All grades can be appealed; final appeal board made up of staff and students</p></li><li><p>Year 3 assessment is a <blank data-qid=\"q25\"/> of 14,000 - 15,000 words. Due 1st day of year 4.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Weekly Workload</strong></p><table><thead><tr><th>2 lectures per module / elective</th><th>All students on the course</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>2 seminars</td><td>15 students approx.</td></tr><tr><td><blank data-qid=\"q26\"/></td><td>5 students approx.</td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>Long working day!!</em></p>",
